<Fragment slot="intro">
<p>Laguna Niguel sits between the coast and inland Orange County — geographically between Laguna Beach and Mission Viejo, and the service calls here reflect that position precisely. The western neighbourhoods — Marina Hills, Laguna Sur, Sea Country near the Ritz-Carlton — get meaningful Pacific salt air that affects gas connectors and vent caps faster than people expect this far from the water. The eastern neighbourhoods — Rancho Niguel, Niguel Hills, Salt Creek, Niguel Summit — are genuinely inland, with a service profile closer to Mission Viejo than Laguna Beach. Laguna Niguel also has a specific architectural character: multi-story homes with upstairs laundry rooms are very common here, especially in the DLGX gas dryer households. When a drum roller goes in an upstairs installation, the noise travels through the floor structure to bedrooms below. We know these multi-story configurations well — we navigate them daily.</p>
